LDG installation

this file has two parts :
1/ How to install LDG on your system
------------- How to instal LDG --------

a) Installing LDG kernel
From cpu folder (68k or coldfire) copy

   - auto/ldg.prg in your auto folder (this is absolutely need for GFA application using LDG)
   - cpx/ldg.cpx in your CPX folder  (work fine with zcontrol or cops but not with xcontrol!!!)
     notice no coldfire version is available at this you should use 68K version under coldfire,
     the CPX is not fully need until you not want change default ldg folder path as define as C:/gemsys/ldg/
   - daemon/ldgd.app anywhere you want : it contains LDGD.APP that
     should be launch automatically by AES on multitask system. It is
     not required on single-TOS
   - gemsys/ldg anywhere you want (probably C:/gemsys this is destination by default). mem.ldg is not native 
   for coldfire at this time.

copy guides/*.hyp and guides/*.ref in your ST-Guide folder

b) Configuring LDG kernel
execute from your desktop auto/ldg.prg
execute cpx/ldg.cpx from Zcontrol or cops and set the correct path
of LDG-libraries : it should be C:/gemsys/ldg but any location is
possible.

c) Installing devel libraries (optional, only for developper)
depending on your compiler, copy the right LDG library in your
compiler libraries folder:
  - with gcc 2.9.5 or higher (MiNT and ext2 filesystem) : copy lib/gcc/*.a in /usr/lib
  - with pure c : copy lib/purec/*.a in your Pure C lib folder
Copy LDG header files include/* in your compiler include folder

If your use an shell command line, you can copy manual file (folder man)
and some utility (folder bin).



